#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-documentation/path-specific/kernel.md:1
msgid "`kernel/`"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-documentation/path-specific/kernel.md:3
msgid "Guidelines that apply only to code under `kernel/`."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-documentation/path-specific/kernel.md:5
msgid "Keep the Linux Compatibility docs current (`linux-compat-docs`)"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-documentation/path-specific/kernel.md:7
msgid ""
"When a change under `kernel/` adds or enhances a user-visible API — a system "
"call or a kernel parameter — update the [Linux Compatibility](../../../../"
"kernel/linux-compatibility/) section in the same PR, so the documented "
"coverage keeps matching the code."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-documentation/path-specific/kernel.md:11
msgid ""
"For a **system call**: update the matching [Syscall Flag Coverage]"
"(../../../../kernel/linux-compatibility/syscall-flag-coverage/) page and its "
"[SCML](../../../../kernel/linux-compatibility/syscall-flag-coverage/system-"
"call-matching-language.md) (`.scml`) coverage file to reflect the newly "
"supported flags, arguments, and behaviors."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-documentation/path-specific/kernel.md:15
msgid ""
"For a **kernel parameter**: update the [Kernel Parameters](../../../../"
"kernel/linux-compatibility/kernel-parameters.md) page."
msgstr ""
